    <string name="disclosure_title">How EarTranslator uses your microphone</string>
    <string name="disclosure_body">EarTranslator listens through your Bluetooth earbud microphone to translate speech in real time.\n\n• All processing happens on this device — speech recognition, translation, and voice are fully offline.\n• Your audio is never recorded, saved, or sent anywhere. This app has no internet access.\n• Bluetooth permissions are used only to find and route audio to your earbuds, never to determine your location.\n\nBy tapping “I agree” you grant microphone and Bluetooth access and accept the Terms of Service and Privacy Policy (available anytime from the home screen).</string>
